{"questionId":"9073042","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate the difference in pressure between X and Y.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Bernoulli: «<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\rho v_x^2\">\n  <mi>ρ</mi>\n  <msubsup>\n    <mi>v</mi>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </msubsup>\n</math></span></span> + 0 + <em>P<span style=\"font-size:11.6667px;\"><sub>x</sub></span></em>&nbsp;=<em>&nbsp;</em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>&nbsp;</em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\rho v_y^2\">\n  <mi>ρ</mi>\n  <msubsup>\n    <mi>v</mi>\n    <mi>y</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </msubsup>\n</math></span></span> +<em> pgH + P<sub>y</sub> » gives P<sub>x</sub>&nbsp;− P<sub>y</sub> = pgH&nbsp;</em>✔</p>\n<p><em>P</em><sub>x</sub> − <em>P</em><sub>y&nbsp;</sub>= 720 × 9.81 × 1.2 = 8.5 «kPa» ✔</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for bald correct answer.</em></p>\n<p><em>Watch for POT mistakes.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073042","referenceCode":"19M.3.HL.TZ1.b.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the difference in pressure between X and Y.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Additional higher level option topics)","B.3 – Fluids and fluid dynamics (HL only)","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Additional higher level option topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders"